[本質記憶]
Implements the W3C CSS View Transitions Level 2 specification for Multi-Page Applications (MPA). The logic operates as a state machine: 1. Rule Registration (mapping domains to NavigationTransitionTrigger), 2. Exit Capture (rasterizing the current DOM state into a TransitionSnapshotBuffer if same-origin and trigger is 'Auto'), and 3. Entry Blending (applying the cached snapshot to the new document's first paint). Includes a telemetry interface for AI-driven spatial memory tracking of cross-document swaps.
===
